Nomura Cuts South Africa’s Economic Growth Forecast for Next Year to 3.4%

-- B y   A n d r e s   R .   M a r t i n e z
-- 
2011-09-15T08:21:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/nomura-cuts-south-africa-2012-economic-growth-forecast-to-3-4-.html
Nomura Plc reduced its forecast for
 South Africa ’s economic growth in 2012 to 3.4 percent from 3.5
percent, it said.  Africa’s biggest economy will probably grow 3.1 percent
this year, Peter Attard Montalto, a London-based economist at
Nomura, said in an e-mailed note to clients today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andres R. Martinez in Mexico City at 
 amartinez28@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
